   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>Subject Fifty-nine PREPARE TO MEET THY GOD Scripture: Amos 4:12 The relationship between God and man God is the creator of man, and God is man s ruler.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>We live and move in Him, and we shall be judged by God.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>This paragraph is to show that our living is related to God.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Man shall meet God Today man doesn t feel that he is related to God.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>You should portray man s condition of dumbness and dullness toward God.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Man is insensitive to God and does not care for God.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Each one will have to leave this world one day.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>When a man dies, his present life is finished, and eternity begins.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>When a man enters eternity, he shall meet God.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>God s judgment When a man meets God, he shall be judged by God.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>God s judgment is according to a man s work.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>No man s work can meet the standard of God s judgment.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>Hence, the result of God s judgment is that man will be condemned to perish.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>How to prepare to meet God Repent and turn to God.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>Confess and forsake your sins.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>Believe and receive Christ and His redemption.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>Serve God.</S>
   </TEXT>
